250 g Mild Italian Sausage, uncased
350 g Cheese Tortellini
1 unit(s) Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic and Onion
113 g Mirepoix
56 g Baby Spinach
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
56 mL Cream
7 g Zesty Garlic Blend
7.5 g Chicken Stock Powder
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
Roughly chop spinach. (TIP: Place spinach in a bowl, then roughly chop using a pair of kitchen shears or scissors!)
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.

Heat a large pot over medium-high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then mirepoix. Cook for 1 min, stirring occasionally, until starting to soften.
Add sausage. Cook for 4-5 min, breaking up sausage into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Season with salt and pepper.

Add garlic, crushed tomatoes, Zesty Garlic Blend, stock powder and 3 1/2 cups (7 cups) water. Stir to combine. (NOTE: Scrape any browned bits from the bottom of the pot, this will add flavour!) Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and bring to a boil over high.

Once soup comes up to a boil, add tortellini. Cook for 2-4 min, stirring occasionally, until tender but still firm to the bite.

Reduce heat to medium. Stir in cream and spinach. Cook for 1 min, stirring often, until spinach wilts. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide soup between bowls.
Sprinkle Parmesan over top.